# Team Glossary

Use these terms consistently in code, comments, documentation, and agent output. When a preferred term exists, use it; do not substitute synonyms.

## People and Entities

| Term | Definition | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| **member** | An insured individual in a health plan. | Preferred over "patient" in claims and enrollment contexts. "Patient" is acceptable only in clinical/provider contexts. |
| **provider** | A clinician or facility that delivers care. | Identified by NPI (CLM_SPRV_NPI). |
| **book** | An insurance product type processed as a unit. | PPO, SPPO, POS, HMO, MEDR. Each book is processed independently through staging. |

## Identifiers

| Term | Column(s) | Definition |
|------|----------|-----------|
| **MEM_NUM** | MEM_NUM | Member number. Unique within a book. BIGINT, though sometimes stored as VARCHAR in source. |
| **MASTERRECORDID** | MASTERRECORDID | Cross-system member identifier. VARCHAR. Used for joins across claims, lanes, and demographics. |
| **MEDSRV_KEY** | MEDSRV_KEY | Medical service key. The standard dedup key for claims. BIGINT. |
| **INT_CLM_NUM** | INT_CLM_NUM | Internal claim number. Groups service lines within a single claim. Not a dedup key on its own. |
| **EPISODE_NUM** | EPISODE_NUM | Episode number assigned by the ETG grouper. |
| **NPI** | CLM_SPRV_NPI | National Provider Identifier for the supervising provider. |

## Insurance Products (Books)

| Code | Full Name | Notes |
|------|----------|-------|
| **PPO** | Preferred Provider Organization | Largest volume. |
| **SPPO** | Select PPO | Variant of PPO. |
| **POS** | Point of Service | |
| **HMO** | Health Maintenance Organization | |
| **MEDR** | Medicare Risk | Also appears as "MEDICARE RISK" in source data. Normalize to "MEDR" via model_mapping. |

## Clinical and Claims Concepts

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **claim** | A billing record for a healthcare service. One claim may have multiple service lines (CLM_LINE_NUM). |
| **service line** | A single line item on a claim, identified by MEDSRV_KEY. |
| **episode** | A clinically related group of services over time, assigned by the ETG grouper. Defined by ETG code, start/end dates, severity, complication, and comorbidity. |
| **ETG** | Episode Treatment Group. A classification system that groups claims into clinically meaningful episodes. Can be truncated to 4 digits for category-level analysis. |
| **lane** | A clinical pathway or care trajectory (e.g., physical therapy, imaging, surgical). Lanes are defined by combinations of diagnoses, procedures, and utilization patterns. |
| **feature** | An event or characteristic within a lane (e.g., "MRI", "injection", "surgery"). |
| **stage** | A severity or progression state assigned to a member at a point in time by the staging engine. Stages have priority (lower wins), persistence (transient/sticky/permanent), and may depend on prior stages. |
| **staging** | The process of assigning members to disease progression stages based on claims, episodes, lanes, and clinical rules. |
| **spur** | A data file partition downloaded from S3. Named after the file prefix pattern used in the source system. |

## Financial Fields

| Term | Column | Definition |
|------|--------|-----------|
| **allowed amount** | DW_ALLOW_AMT | The total amount the plan agrees to pay for a service. |
| **liability** | DW_TOTAL_LIAB_AMT | The plan's financial liability for the service. |
| **coinsurance** | COINS_AMT | Member's coinsurance portion. |
| **copay** | COPAY_AMT | Member's copay portion. |
| **deductible** | DEDUCT_AMT | Amount applied to the member's deductible. |
| **PMPM** | (derived) | Per Member Per Month. A standard actuarial normalization for cost. |

## Date Fields

| Term | Column | Format | Notes |
|------|--------|--------|-------|
| **incurred date** | INCURRED_DT_DAY | `'01JAN2024'` (SAS) or DATE | The date the service was provided. Parse with `strptime(INCURRED_DT_DAY, '%d%b%Y')` unless the column is already DATE type. Always check type before parsing. |
| **admission dates** | DW_ADM_FROM_DT, DW_ADM_TO_DT | VARCHAR | Facility admission and discharge dates. |
| **episode dates** | EPI_START_DT, EPI_END_DT | VARCHAR | Episode boundary dates from the ETG grouper. |
| **anchor date** | ANCHOR_LBP_DT | DATE | Reference date for relative time calculations in lane analysis. |

## Reference Data

All canonical reference data lives in `ReferenceData/reference.duckdb`, organized by payer schema: `medicare`, `commercial`, `ndc`, `elixhauser`, `geography` (all populated), `medicaid` (placeholder). Access via `ReferenceData.reference_db`, which defaults to the `medicare` schema. Full column-level documentation is in `ReferenceData/DATA_DICTIONARY.md`. The database is built from a separate build script (see `ReferenceData/DATA_DICTIONARY.md`).

| Table | Contents | Use |
|-------|---------|-----|
| **cpt_cd** | 32,654 CPT codes with GROUP_CAT_CD, GROUP_SUB_CD | Procedure categorization |
| **revenue_cd** | 321 revenue codes with GROUP_CAT_CD, GROUP_SUB_CD | Facility billing classification |
| **bill_type** | 679 bill type codes with TREND_CAT_CD, FACILITY_TYPE, BILL_CLASSIFICATION | IP/OP/HH/SNF determination |
| **bill_type_hs** | 679 bill type codes (health system variant) | Health system-specific IP/OP/HH/SNF |
| **ms_drg** | 799 Medicare Severity DRGs with DRG_WGHT, GEO_LOS, AVG_LOS | Inpatient case mix |
| **cms_drg** | 581 CMS DRGs | Older DRG classification |
| **ap_drg** | 1,398 All Patient DRGs with severity levels | Alternative DRG grouping |
| **chronic_dx** | 3,484 chronic condition diagnosis codes with CC_IND, SOURCE | Chronic disease identification |
| **category_mapping** | 236 trend-to-group category crosswalk | Cost trend reporting |
| **pot_cd** | 99 place of treatment codes with TREND_CAT_CD, location descriptors | Care setting classification |
| **discharge_status** | 99 discharge status codes with descriptions | Post-acute disposition |
| **esrd_cpt** | 95 ESRD CPT codes | ESRD identification |
| **ltch** | 426 long-term care hospital facilities with CMS_CCN | LTCH identification |
| **clm_cat_lookups** | 236 claims categorization codes (ER, SNF, HH, IRF, Room and Board revenue codes; specialty and taxonomy codes) | Claims categorization (parsed from legacy CLM_CAT_LKPS.sas) |
| **revenue_code_flags** (view) | Revenue codes with boolean is_er, is_snf, is_hh, is_irf, is_room_board flags | Revenue code categorization |

## Platform and Architecture

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **Unity Catalog** | Databricks governance layer. Used for access control, lineage, and IP protection. |
| **UC function** | A Python or SQL function registered in Unity Catalog. Used to encapsulate reusable logic (risk scores, cost models) with controlled access grants. |
| **Asset Bundle** | Databricks Asset Bundle (DAB). The deployment artifact for promoting code across environments. |
| **clean room** | A Databricks Clean Room where validated code runs against sensitive data in isolation. |
| **medallion architecture** | Bronze (raw ingestion), Silver (standardized), Gold (analytics-ready). Used in both DBT models and Delta Lake tables. |
| **Tuva** | Open-source healthcare data model used for standardization (medical_claim, pharmacy_claim, eligibility). |

